  "text": "where P a is power absorbed by the processing materials, the P f is power fed into the system. The NPA grid size changes are shown in Figure 3 . The manual of the software QuickWave (QuickWave v6.0, QWED, Warsaw, Poland) recommends 12 cells per wavelength for grid-independent results, while other studies [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] indicate that 10 cells per wavelength are sufficient. Here, both the NPA with mesh size and the calculation time are studied and shown in Figure 3 . According to the mesh independent study, the mesh size used in this paper is defined as:",
